  "reveal": {
    "brief_voiced": "Fifi Swain stands accused, and the table condemns her. The pistol at Dr Tobias Quill's place—the fifth upon the host's right—lay charged against the Colonel's protocol, which demands that no loaded weapon sit beside a lady. Yet Fifi Swain occupied the fourth place upon that same right hand, and the charged pistol fell within her reach. She sat directly across from Nan Pringle, who held the fourth place upon the left.\n\nFifi, a lady's-maid and twin to Zane, hears more than a servant ought. Nan Pringle, the Colonel's poor relation, pours the tea and keeps the accounts, missing nothing. What Nan heard or saw—what secrets a servant in the household learns—proved a threat that could not stand. A woman who listens and remembers is dangerous to those with something to hide.\n\nThe case is closed.",
